<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Ghana </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rawlings Rejects Education Minister's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rawlings Rejects Education Minister's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0506163094 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in English 1300 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0506163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president, Flight Lieutenant Jerry John 
Rawlings, has rejected the resignation from government of the 
minister of education, Mr. Harry Sawyerr. This is in response 
to the minister's letter of resignation, tendered on Friday, 
June 3, over the strike action by teachers. The president's 
reaction is contained in a statement issued in Accra today, and 
signed by the deputy minister of information, Mr. Kojo Yankah. 
The statement said the president affirmed his confidence in Mr. 
Sawyerr's ability to handle the issues confronting his ministry, 
and that this is not the time to pull out. It quoted the 
president has saying: We need to collectively continue to meet 
the challenges of the times. 

</TEXT>

